===========================================
        HERLIFE CYCLE NUTRITION PLANNER
===========================================

What you eat can drastically improve how you feel throughout your cycle. 
Use this guide to plan your meals according to your body's changing hormonal needs.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 1: MENSTRUATION (Days 1-5)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Your body is losing blood and shedding its lining. Focus on replenishing minerals.

Foods to Focus On:
- Iron-Rich Foods: Red meat, lentils, spinach, kale, pumpkin seeds.
- Vitamin C (helps iron absorption): Citrus fruits, bell peppers, broccoli.
- Anti-inflammatory Fats: Wild-caught salmon, avocado, walnuts.
- Warm, Comforting Foods: Soups, stews, root vegetables, herbal teas.

Avoid: Alcohol, highly processed foods, excess caffeine (can worsen cramps).

----------------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 2: FOLLICULAR PHASE (Days 6-13)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Estrogen is rising. Your body needs light, fresh foods to support energy.

Foods to Focus On:
- Sprouted grains and light grains (oats, quinoa).
- Fermented Foods (for gut health): Kimchi, sauerkraut, kefir, kombucha.
- Fresh Vegetables: Salads, zucchini, string beans, broccoli.
- Lean Proteins: Chicken, eggs, tofu.

Avoid: Heavy, greasy meals that might make you feel sluggish.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 3: OVULATION (Day 14)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Hormones are at their peak. Your liver is working hard to process the excess estrogen.

Foods to Focus On:
- Liver-Supporting Veggies: Broccoli, cauliflower, Brussels sprouts, kale.
- Fiber-Rich Foods: Chia seeds, flaxseeds, berries (helps flush out estrogen).
- Raw Foods: Smoothies, fresh juices, raw salads.
- Antioxidants: Dark chocolate (70%+), berries, green tea.

Avoid: Excess sugar and simple carbs that might cause an energy crash.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 4: LUTEAL PHASE (Days 15-28)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Progesterone rises, which can slow digestion and increase cravings. Metabolism is slightly higher.

Foods to Focus On:
- Complex Carbs (to stabilize blood sugar & serotonin): Sweet potatoes, brown rice, squash.
- Magnesium-Rich Foods (to combat PMS/cramps): Dark chocolate, spinach, pumpkin seeds, black beans.
- B-Vitamins: Chickpeas, bananas, grass-fed beef.
- Calcium: Yogurt, almonds, leafy greens.

Avoid: Too much salt (causes bloating) and excessive caffeine (increases anxiety).

